id: swarm-code-fix-v1
name: 10-Domain Parallel Fixer Swarm v1.5
version: 1.5
workflow_objective: Apply targeted code fixes across all 10 review domains in parallel, then open a single consolidated PR with rollback safety, cross-domain awareness, and self-verification.
description: |
  Mirrors the swarm-code-review-v3 agent roster: one dedicated fixer per domain.
  All 10 fixers run in parallel after setup. A consolidate-pr agent waits for all fixers,
  runs integration build/test, bisects on failure, and opens a single PR.

  v1.5: Precision fixes from review:
    - Fix 1: qwen-plus → minimax-m2.7:cloud for docs/ux/product (qwen-plus unproven in antfarm)
    - Fix 2: STATUS:partial for multi-file fixes (revert only failing file, not entire fix)
    - Fix 3: post-review scoped to changed domains only, not all changed files
  v1.4: Issue 6 — post-consolidation re-review loop properly wired as a real workflow step.
    - Added post-review agent + step (depends_on: consolidate-pr)
    - verify=true triggers targeted review of ONLY changed files on the fix branch
    - Asks: "did combined fixes introduce NEW issues?" (distinct from per-fixer self-verification)
    - VERIFY_STATUS fed back into PR comment via consolidator output
    - verify=false (default): post-review step outputs VERIFY_STATUS: skipped immediately
  v1.3: Precision corrections from review (Issues 1-5):
    - Issue 1: priority default changed all (was high-and-above — was silently skipping medium findings)
    - Issue 2: self-verification extended to all modified files, not just single file
    - Issue 3: confirmed — bisect only triggers on build failure (safe_consolidate guards Step 3)
    - Issue 4: fix-docs/fix-ux/fix-product downgraded qwen3.5→qwen-plus (right-sized)
    - Issue 5: confirmed — all model strings have :cloud suffix (qwen-plus has no suffix, correct)
  v1.2: Principal-engineer structural upgrades (Fas priority order):
    - #2 Rollback: consolidator runs full build+test after merge; bisects failing domains;
      DOMAINS_EXCLUDED field; opt-in via safe_consolidate=true (default true).
    - #1 Cross-domain: all fixers receive full findings (read-only) + shared-file map from setup.
    - #5 Re-review loop: verify=true flag added; design decision: --context verify=true triggers
      targeted re-review of affected domains after consolidator finishes (separate from full swarm).
      Consolidator output includes VERIFY_STATUS field when verify=true.
      Setup now detects files appearing in multiple domain findings and flags them.
    - #5 Re-review: each fixer has explicit self-verification step — re-reads edited file,
      confirms the specific cited issue is resolved before committing.
    - #3 Severity ordering: PR body organized security→backend→perf→tests→code-quality
      →frontend→devops→ux→product→docs. Deferred items at bottom.
    - #6 Deferred tracking: consolidator aggregates all STATUS:deferred outputs into
      DEFERRED_LOG section in PR body with full context for next run.
    - #4 Max fixes: default 3→5; priority default=all (all findings); high-and-above/high/critical-only for fast passes.
    - #7 Setup model: qwen-turbo (4 git commands don't need qwen3.5).
  v1.1: Model alignment + PE prompt elevation.
  v1.0: Initial release — domain-matched fixers, Bug #17/#21/#22/#27 fixed.

context:
  repo_path: ""          # REQUIRED: --repo-path=/path/to/repo
  repo_name: ""          # REQUIRED: --context repo_name=my-project
  findings: ""           # REQUIRED: --context findings="$(cat findings.txt)"
  branch: "fix/swarm-auto"
  build_cmd: "npm run build 2>/dev/null || python -m py_compile **/*.py 2>/dev/null || true"
  test_cmd: "npm test --passWithNoTests 2>/dev/null || pytest -x -q 2>/dev/null || true"
  exclude_patterns: "_build_artifacts,node_modules,vendor,.venv,__pycache__,dist,build,.next,.git"
  max_fixes_per_domain: "5"          # v1.2: bumped from 3
  priority: "all"                     # options: all (default) | high-and-above | high (high+critical) | critical-only
  safe_consolidate: "true"           # run bisect rollback on integration build failure
  verify: "false"                    # set true to trigger targeted re-review after PR opens
  fix_directive: "Fix real issues found in {{ repo_path }}. Read files before editing. Exclude: {{ exclude_patterns }}. Do NOT fabricate fixes. Do NOT discuss the workflow pipeline."

acceptance_criteria:
  - "Setup creates branch, confirms repo accessible, outputs shared-file map"
  - "All 10 fixer agents complete (partial ok — consolidator handles missing/deferred)"
  - "Each fixer outputs STATUS: done | skipped | deferred"
  - "consolidate-pr runs integration build before opening PR"
  - "If safe_consolidate=true and build fails: bisect, exclude breaking domain, still open PR"
  - "PR body ordered by severity; DEFERRED_LOG section present if any items deferred"
  - "No fixer rewrites files in node_modules / vendor / _build_artifacts"
  - "If verify=true: post-review step runs against changed files only; outputs VERIFY_STATUS"

polling:
  model: ollama-cloud/qwen3.5:397b-cloud
  timeoutSeconds: 7200

agents:
  - id: setup
    name: Setup
    role: setup
    workspace:
      baseDir: agents/setup
      files:
        AGENTS.md: agents/setup/AGENTS.md
    model: ollama-cloud/qwen-turbo  # v1.2: git ops don't need qwen3.5

  - id: fix-code-quality
    name: Code Quality Fixer
    role: fix
    workspace:
      baseDir: agents/fix-code-quality
      files:
        AGENTS.md: agents/fix-code-quality/AGENTS.md
    model: ollama-cloud/qwen3.5:397b-cloud

  - id: fix-security
    name: Security Fixer
    role: fix
    workspace:
      baseDir: agents/fix-security
      files:
        AGENTS.md: agents/fix-security/AGENTS.md
    model: ollama-cloud/qwen3.5:397b-cloud

  - id: fix-performance
    name: Performance Fixer
    role: fix
    workspace:
      baseDir: agents/fix-performance
      files:
        AGENTS.md: agents/fix-performance/AGENTS.md
    model: ollama-cloud/devstral-2:123b-cloud

  - id: fix-ux
    name: UX Fixer
    role: fix
    workspace:
      baseDir: agents/fix-ux
      files:
        AGENTS.md: agents/fix-ux/AGENTS.md
    model: ollama-cloud/minimax-m2.7:cloud  # Tier 3 — proven, configured

  - id: fix-backend
    name: Backend Fixer
    role: fix
    workspace:
      baseDir: agents/fix-backend
      files:
        AGENTS.md: agents/fix-backend/AGENTS.md
    model: ollama-cloud/qwen3.5:397b-cloud

  - id: fix-frontend
    name: Frontend Fixer
    role: fix
    workspace:
      baseDir: agents/fix-frontend
      files:
        AGENTS.md: agents/fix-frontend/AGENTS.md
    model: ollama-cloud/qwen3.5:397b-cloud

  - id: fix-devops
    name: DevOps Fixer
    role: fix
    workspace:
      baseDir: agents/fix-devops
      files:
        AGENTS.md: agents/fix-devops/AGENTS.md
    model: ollama-cloud/qwen3.5:397b-cloud

  - id: fix-docs
    name: Documentation Fixer
    role: fix
    workspace:
      baseDir: agents/fix-docs
      files:
        AGENTS.md: agents/fix-docs/AGENTS.md
    model: ollama-cloud/minimax-m2.7:cloud  # Tier 3 — proven, configured

  - id: fix-tests
    name: Testing Fixer
    role: fix
    workspace:
      baseDir: agents/fix-tests
      files:
        AGENTS.md: agents/fix-tests/AGENTS.md
    model: ollama-cloud/qwen3.5:397b-cloud

  - id: fix-product
    name: Product Fixer
    role: fix
    workspace:
      baseDir: agents/fix-product
      files:
        AGENTS.md: agents/fix-product/AGENTS.md
    model: ollama-cloud/minimax-m2.7:cloud  # Tier 3 — proven, configured

  - id: consolidate-pr
    name: PR Consolidator
    role: pr
    workspace:
      baseDir: agents/consolidate-pr
      files:
        AGENTS.md: agents/consolidate-pr/AGENTS.md
    model: ollama-cloud/qwen3.5:397b-cloud

  - id: post-review
    name: Post-Fix Reviewer
    role: review
    workspace:
      baseDir: agents/post-review
      files:
        AGENTS.md: agents/post-review/AGENTS.md
    model: ollama-cloud/devstral-2:123b-cloud  # Code review needs strong analysis, not just generation

steps:
  - id: setup
    agent: setup
    expects: 'SETUP_OK:'
    timeoutSeconds: 300
    max_retries: 2
    input: |
      TASK: {{ task }}
      REPO_PATH: {{ repo_path }}
      REPO_NAME: {{ repo_name }}
      BRANCH: {{ branch }}
      EXCLUDE: {{ exclude_patterns }}
      ALL_FINDINGS: {{ findings }}

      {{ fix_directive }}

      STEP 1: cd {{ repo_path }} — confirm the directory exists.
      STEP 2: git status — confirm it is a git repo.
      STEP 3: git checkout -b {{ branch }} 2>/dev/null || git checkout {{ branch }}
      STEP 4: Shared-file detection — scan ALL_FINDINGS above and identify any file paths
        that appear in findings from more than one domain. Output a SHARED_FILES: list.
        These are high-conflict-risk files — downstream fixers will use this map.

      Output format:
        SETUP_OK: branch={{ branch }} repo={{ repo_path }}
        SHARED_FILES: file1.py (security+backend), file2.ts (frontend+ux), ...
        If no shared files: SHARED_FILES: none

  - id: fix-code-quality
    agent: fix-code-quality
    depends_on: [setup]
    expects: 'STATUS:'
    timeoutSeconds: 3600
    max_retries: 2
    input: |
      TASK: {{ task }}
      REPO_PATH: {{ repo_path }}
      REPO_NAME: {{ repo_name }}
      BRANCH: {{ branch }}
      BUILD_CMD: {{ build_cmd }}
      TEST_CMD: {{ test_cmd }}
      EXCLUDE: {{ exclude_patterns }}
      MAX_FIXES: {{ max_fixes_per_domain }}
      PRIORITY: {{ priority }}

      {{ fix_directive }}

      CROSS_DOMAIN_CONTEXT (read-only — do NOT fix these, just be aware):
      {{ findings }}
      SHARED_FILES (appear in multiple domains — edit minimally): {{ steps.setup.summary }}

      YOUR DOMAIN FINDINGS (code-quality only — fix these):
      {{ findings }}

      Filter YOUR DOMAIN section to only code-quality findings.
      Apply PRIORITY filter:
      - all (default): fix all severities
      - high-and-above: fix high + critical, skip medium/low
      - high: fix high + critical only (synonym for high-and-above, explicit)
      - critical-only: fix only critical findings
      Skip anything below your priority threshold — do NOT defer it, just skip it.
      Fix the top {{ max_fixes_per_domain }} matching findings.
      Before editing any SHARED_FILE, check git log to see if another fixer already touched it.
      If no code-quality findings match, output STATUS: skipped — no findings for this domain.

  - id: fix-security
    agent: fix-security
    depends_on: [setup]
    expects: 'STATUS:'
    timeoutSeconds: 3600
    max_retries: 2
    input: |
      TASK: {{ task }}
      REPO_PATH: {{ repo_path }}
      REPO_NAME: {{ repo_name }}
      BRANCH: {{ branch }}
      BUILD_CMD: {{ build_cmd }}
      TEST_CMD: {{ test_cmd }}
      EXCLUDE: {{ exclude_patterns }}
      MAX_FIXES: {{ max_fixes_per_domain }}
      PRIORITY: {{ priority }}

      {{ fix_directive }}

      CROSS_DOMAIN_CONTEXT (read-only — do NOT fix these, just be aware):
      {{ findings }}
      SHARED_FILES (appear in multiple domains — edit minimally): {{ steps.setup.summary }}

      YOUR DOMAIN FINDINGS (security only — fix these):
      {{ findings }}

      Filter YOUR DOMAIN section to only security findings.
      Apply PRIORITY filter:
      - all (default): fix all severities
      - high-and-above: fix high + critical, skip medium/low
      - high: fix high + critical only (synonym for high-and-above, explicit)
      - critical-only: fix only critical findings
      Skip anything below your priority threshold — do NOT defer it, just skip it.
      Fix the top {{ max_fixes_per_domain }} matching findings.
      For each security fix, write a regression test that proves the attack vector is blocked.
      Before editing any SHARED_FILE, check git log to see if another fixer already touched it.
      If no security findings match, output STATUS: skipped — no findings for this domain.

  - id: fix-performance
    agent: fix-performance
    depends_on: [setup]
    expects: 'STATUS:'
    timeoutSeconds: 3600
    max_retries: 2
    input: |
      TASK: {{ task }}
      REPO_PATH: {{ repo_path }}
      REPO_NAME: {{ repo_name }}
      BRANCH: {{ branch }}
      BUILD_CMD: {{ build_cmd }}
      TEST_CMD: {{ test_cmd }}
      EXCLUDE: {{ exclude_patterns }}
      MAX_FIXES: {{ max_fixes_per_domain }}
      PRIORITY: {{ priority }}

      {{ fix_directive }}

      CROSS_DOMAIN_CONTEXT (read-only — do NOT fix these, just be aware):
      {{ findings }}
      SHARED_FILES (appear in multiple domains — edit minimally): {{ steps.setup.summary }}

      YOUR DOMAIN FINDINGS (performance only — fix these):
      {{ findings }}

      Filter YOUR DOMAIN section to only performance findings.
      Apply PRIORITY filter:
      - all (default): fix all severities
      - high-and-above: fix high + critical, skip medium/low
      - high: fix high + critical only (synonym for high-and-above, explicit)
      - critical-only: fix only critical findings
      Skip anything below your priority threshold — do NOT defer it, just skip it.
      Fix the top {{ max_fixes_per_domain }} matching findings.
      Before editing any SHARED_FILE, check git log to see if another fixer already touched it.
      If no performance findings match, output STATUS: skipped — no findings for this domain.

  - id: fix-ux
    agent: fix-ux
    depends_on: [setup]
    expects: 'STATUS:'
    timeoutSeconds: 3600
    max_retries: 2
    input: |
      TASK: {{ task }}
      REPO_PATH: {{ repo_path }}
      REPO_NAME: {{ repo_name }}
      BRANCH: {{ branch }}
      BUILD_CMD: {{ build_cmd }}
      TEST_CMD: {{ test_cmd }}
      EXCLUDE: {{ exclude_patterns }}
      MAX_FIXES: {{ max_fixes_per_domain }}
      PRIORITY: {{ priority }}

      {{ fix_directive }}

      CROSS_DOMAIN_CONTEXT (read-only — do NOT fix these, just be aware):
      {{ findings }}
      SHARED_FILES (appear in multiple domains — edit minimally): {{ steps.setup.summary }}

      YOUR DOMAIN FINDINGS (ux only — fix these):
      {{ findings }}

      Filter YOUR DOMAIN section to only UX findings (accessibility, error states, form validation).
      Apply PRIORITY filter:
      - all (default): fix all severities
      - high-and-above: fix high + critical, skip medium/low
      - high: fix high + critical only (synonym for high-and-above, explicit)
      - critical-only: fix only critical findings
      Skip anything below your priority threshold — do NOT defer it, just skip it.
      Fix the top {{ max_fixes_per_domain }} matching findings.
      Before editing any SHARED_FILE, check git log to see if another fixer already touched it.
      If no UX findings match, output STATUS: skipped — no findings for this domain.

  - id: fix-backend
    agent: fix-backend
    depends_on: [setup]
    expects: 'STATUS:'
    timeoutSeconds: 3600
    max_retries: 2
    input: |
      TASK: {{ task }}
      REPO_PATH: {{ repo_path }}
      REPO_NAME: {{ repo_name }}
      BRANCH: {{ branch }}
      BUILD_CMD: {{ build_cmd }}
      TEST_CMD: {{ test_cmd }}
      EXCLUDE: {{ exclude_patterns }}
      MAX_FIXES: {{ max_fixes_per_domain }}
      PRIORITY: {{ priority }}

      {{ fix_directive }}

      CROSS_DOMAIN_CONTEXT (read-only — do NOT fix these, just be aware):
      {{ findings }}
      SHARED_FILES (appear in multiple domains — edit minimally): {{ steps.setup.summary }}

      YOUR DOMAIN FINDINGS (backend only — fix these):
      {{ findings }}

      Filter YOUR DOMAIN section to only backend findings (API design, error handling, DB schema, Lambda).
      Apply PRIORITY filter:
      - all (default): fix all severities
      - high-and-above: fix high + critical, skip medium/low
      - high: fix high + critical only (synonym for high-and-above, explicit)
      - critical-only: fix only critical findings
      Skip anything below your priority threshold — do NOT defer it, just skip it.
      Fix the top {{ max_fixes_per_domain }} matching findings.
      Before editing any SHARED_FILE, check git log to see if another fixer already touched it.
      If no backend findings match, output STATUS: skipped — no findings for this domain.

  - id: fix-frontend
    agent: fix-frontend
    depends_on: [setup]
    expects: 'STATUS:'
    timeoutSeconds: 3600
    max_retries: 2
    input: |
      TASK: {{ task }}
      REPO_PATH: {{ repo_path }}
      REPO_NAME: {{ repo_name }}
      BRANCH: {{ branch }}
      BUILD_CMD: {{ build_cmd }}
      TEST_CMD: {{ test_cmd }}
      EXCLUDE: {{ exclude_patterns }}
      MAX_FIXES: {{ max_fixes_per_domain }}
      PRIORITY: {{ priority }}

      {{ fix_directive }}

      CROSS_DOMAIN_CONTEXT (read-only — do NOT fix these, just be aware):
      {{ findings }}
      SHARED_FILES (appear in multiple domains — edit minimally): {{ steps.setup.summary }}

      YOUR DOMAIN FINDINGS (frontend only — fix these):
      {{ findings }}

      Filter YOUR DOMAIN section to only frontend findings (component architecture, state, routing, bundle).
      Apply PRIORITY filter:
      - all (default): fix all severities
      - high-and-above: fix high + critical, skip medium/low
      - high: fix high + critical only (synonym for high-and-above, explicit)
      - critical-only: fix only critical findings
      Skip anything below your priority threshold — do NOT defer it, just skip it.
      Fix the top {{ max_fixes_per_domain }} matching findings.
      Before editing any SHARED_FILE, check git log to see if another fixer already touched it.
      If no frontend findings match, output STATUS: skipped — no findings for this domain.

  - id: fix-devops
    agent: fix-devops
    depends_on: [setup]
    expects: 'STATUS:'
    timeoutSeconds: 3600
    max_retries: 2
    input: |
      TASK: {{ task }}
      REPO_PATH: {{ repo_path }}
      REPO_NAME: {{ repo_name }}
      BRANCH: {{ branch }}
      BUILD_CMD: {{ build_cmd }}
      TEST_CMD: {{ test_cmd }}
      EXCLUDE: {{ exclude_patterns }}
      MAX_FIXES: {{ max_fixes_per_domain }}
      PRIORITY: {{ priority }}

      {{ fix_directive }}

      CROSS_DOMAIN_CONTEXT (read-only — do NOT fix these, just be aware):
      {{ findings }}
      SHARED_FILES (appear in multiple domains — edit minimally): {{ steps.setup.summary }}

      YOUR DOMAIN FINDINGS (devops only — fix these):
      {{ findings }}

      Filter YOUR DOMAIN section to only DevOps findings (CI/CD, IaC, Docker, secrets, monitoring).
      Apply PRIORITY filter:
      - all (default): fix all severities
      - high-and-above: fix high + critical, skip medium/low
      - high: fix high + critical only (synonym for high-and-above, explicit)
      - critical-only: fix only critical findings
      Skip anything below your priority threshold — do NOT defer it, just skip it.
      Fix the top {{ max_fixes_per_domain }} matching findings.
      Before editing any SHARED_FILE, check git log to see if another fixer already touched it.
      If no DevOps findings match, output STATUS: skipped — no findings for this domain.

  - id: fix-docs
    agent: fix-docs
    depends_on: [setup]
    expects: 'STATUS:'
    timeoutSeconds: 1800
    max_retries: 2
    input: |
      TASK: {{ task }}
      REPO_PATH: {{ repo_path }}
      REPO_NAME: {{ repo_name }}
      BRANCH: {{ branch }}
      EXCLUDE: {{ exclude_patterns }}
      MAX_FIXES: {{ max_fixes_per_domain }}
      PRIORITY: {{ priority }}

      {{ fix_directive }}

      CROSS_DOMAIN_CONTEXT (read-only — do NOT fix these, just be aware):
      {{ findings }}
      SHARED_FILES (appear in multiple domains — edit minimally): {{ steps.setup.summary }}

      YOUR DOMAIN FINDINGS (documentation only — fix these):
      {{ findings }}

      Filter YOUR DOMAIN section to only documentation findings.
      Apply PRIORITY filter:
      - all (default): fix all severities
      - high-and-above: fix high + critical, skip medium/low
      - high: fix high + critical only (synonym for high-and-above, explicit)
      - critical-only: fix only critical findings
      Skip anything below your priority threshold — do NOT defer it, just skip it.
      Fix the top {{ max_fixes_per_domain }} matching findings.
      If no documentation findings match, output STATUS: skipped — no findings for this domain.

  - id: fix-tests
    agent: fix-tests
    depends_on: [setup]
    expects: 'STATUS:'
    timeoutSeconds: 3600
    max_retries: 2
    input: |
      TASK: {{ task }}
      REPO_PATH: {{ repo_path }}
      REPO_NAME: {{ repo_name }}
      BRANCH: {{ branch }}
      BUILD_CMD: {{ build_cmd }}
      TEST_CMD: {{ test_cmd }}
      EXCLUDE: {{ exclude_patterns }}
      MAX_FIXES: {{ max_fixes_per_domain }}
      PRIORITY: {{ priority }}

      {{ fix_directive }}

      CROSS_DOMAIN_CONTEXT (read-only — do NOT fix these, just be aware):
      {{ findings }}
      SHARED_FILES (appear in multiple domains — edit minimally): {{ steps.setup.summary }}

      YOUR DOMAIN FINDINGS (testing only — fix these):
      {{ findings }}

      Filter YOUR DOMAIN section to only testing findings (missing coverage, untested paths).
      Apply PRIORITY filter:
      - all (default): fix all severities
      - high-and-above: fix high + critical, skip medium/low
      - high: fix high + critical only (synonym for high-and-above, explicit)
      - critical-only: fix only critical findings
      Skip anything below your priority threshold — do NOT defer it, just skip it.
      Write the top {{ max_fixes_per_domain }} missing tests. Run {{ test_cmd }} after writing.
      If no testing findings match, output STATUS: skipped — no findings for this domain.

  - id: fix-product
    agent: fix-product
    depends_on: [setup]
    expects: 'STATUS:'
    timeoutSeconds: 1800
    max_retries: 2
    input: |
      TASK: {{ task }}
      REPO_PATH: {{ repo_path }}
      REPO_NAME: {{ repo_name }}
      BRANCH: {{ branch }}
      EXCLUDE: {{ exclude_patterns }}
      MAX_FIXES: {{ max_fixes_per_domain }}
      PRIORITY: {{ priority }}

      {{ fix_directive }}

      CROSS_DOMAIN_CONTEXT (read-only — do NOT fix these, just be aware):
      {{ findings }}
      SHARED_FILES (appear in multiple domains — edit minimally): {{ steps.setup.summary }}

      YOUR DOMAIN FINDINGS (product only — fix these):
      {{ findings }}

      Filter YOUR DOMAIN section to only product findings (feature flags, broken flows, hardcoded copy).
      Apply PRIORITY filter:
      - all (default): fix all severities
      - high-and-above: fix high + critical, skip medium/low
      - high: fix high + critical only (synonym for high-and-above, explicit)
      - critical-only: fix only critical findings
      Skip anything below your priority threshold — do NOT defer it, just skip it.
      Fix the top {{ max_fixes_per_domain }} matching findings.
      If no product findings match, output STATUS: skipped — no findings for this domain.

  - id: consolidate-pr
    agent: consolidate-pr
    depends_on:
      - fix-code-quality
      - fix-security
      - fix-performance
      - fix-ux
      - fix-backend
      - fix-frontend
      - fix-devops
      - fix-docs
      - fix-tests
      - fix-product
    expects: 'PR_URL:'
    timeoutSeconds: 2700   # 45 min — allows bisect cycles
    max_retries: 2
    input: |
      TASK: Consolidate all domain fixes into one PR with rollback safety and severity ordering.
      REPO_PATH: {{ repo_path }}
      REPO_NAME: {{ repo_name }}
      BRANCH: {{ branch }}
      BUILD_CMD: {{ build_cmd }}
      TEST_CMD: {{ test_cmd }}
      SAFE_CONSOLIDATE: {{ safe_consolidate }}
      VERIFY: {{ verify }}

      FIXER OUTPUTS (use for PR body + bisect decisions):
      Security: {{ steps.fix-security.summary }}
      Backend: {{ steps.fix-backend.summary }}
      Performance: {{ steps.fix-performance.summary }}
      Testing: {{ steps.fix-tests.summary }}
      Code Quality: {{ steps.fix-code-quality.summary }}
      Frontend: {{ steps.fix-frontend.summary }}
      DevOps: {{ steps.fix-devops.summary }}
      UX: {{ steps.fix-ux.summary }}
      Product: {{ steps.fix-product.summary }}
      Docs: {{ steps.fix-docs.summary }}

      Follow the consolidator protocol in your AGENTS.md:
      1. Run integration build+test
      2. If failure and SAFE_CONSOLIDATE=true: bisect by domain
      3. Order PR body by severity (security first, docs last)
      4. Collect all STATUS:deferred items into DEFERRED_LOG
      5. Open PR

  - id: post-review
    agent: post-review
    depends_on: [consolidate-pr]
    expects: 'VERIFY_STATUS:'
    timeoutSeconds: 3600
    max_retries: 1
    input: |
      TASK: Post-fix system-level review — check whether combined fixes introduced new issues.
      REPO_PATH: {{ repo_path }}
      REPO_NAME: {{ repo_name }}
      BRANCH: {{ branch }}
      BUILD_CMD: {{ build_cmd }}
      TEST_CMD: {{ test_cmd }}
      VERIFY: {{ verify }}
      EXCLUDE: {{ exclude_patterns }}
      ORIGINAL_FINDINGS: {{ findings }}
      SHARED_FILES: {{ steps.setup.summary }}

      CONSOLIDATOR_OUTPUT: {{ steps.consolidate-pr.summary }}
      # consolidator output includes PR_URL:, DOMAINS_INCLUDED:, DOMAINS_EXCLUDED:, DOMAINS_SKIPPED:
      # post-review MUST check DOMAINS_EXCLUDED before deciding what to re-review

      If VERIFY=false: immediately output VERIFY_STATUS: skipped and NEW_ISSUES: 0. Do nothing else.

      If VERIFY=true:
      - DOMAINS_WITH_CHANGES: extract which domains output STATUS:done from fixer summaries above
        (security, backend, performance, testing, code-quality, frontend, devops, ux, product, docs)
      - Get changed files per domain by inspecting FILES_MODIFIED from each fixer output
      - Run review agents ONLY for domains that made changes — do NOT re-review unchanged domains
      - For each changed domain: review only that domain's FILES_MODIFIED for NEW issues
      - Run {{ test_cmd }} to catch regressions across the combined changeset
      - Output VERIFY_STATUS: clean | issues-found with VERIFY_DOMAINS_CHECKED listing only active domains
